  <h2>What broke / what I'd change</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Tool selection errors on ambiguous data.</strong> The agent occasionally selected the wrong statistical test for edge cases — running a Pearson correlation on a heavily skewed variable where Spearman was more appropriate. Adding a pre-flight data characterisation step (normality test, skewness check) before tool selection reduced this significantly.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Sandbox cold start latency.</strong> Docker container startup adds ~2–3 seconds per execution. For a session with 10+ code executions this is noticeable. A warm container pool (pre-started, reused per session, destroyed at session end) would fix this.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Report quality is the output that matters.</strong> Early versions produced technically correct analyses but poorly structured reports — too much raw output, not enough narrative. Investing in the report generation prompt and adding a dedicated "narrative synthesis" node at the end of the ReAct loop produced dramatically better output.
  </p>

